@startuml
title Development View - Event-Driven Component Diagram

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

package "Application Services" {
  component "LoanApplicationService" as LoanSvc
  component "FundTransferService" as TransferSvc
  component "AccountManagementService" as AccountSvc
  component "InterestPostingService" as InterestSvc
}

package "Domain Events" {
  component "LoanApplicationSubmittedEvent" as LoanSubmitted
  component "LoanApprovedEvent / LoanRejectedEvent" as LoanDecision
  component "FundTransferCompletedEvent" as TransferDone
  component "AccountStatusChangedEvent" as AccountChanged
  component "InterestPostedEvent" as InterestPosted
}

package "Event Bus" {
  interface "EventDispatcher" as EventDispatcher
  component "SynchronousEventDispatcher" as SyncBus
}

package "Event Handlers" {
  component "AuditLogEventHandler" as Audit
  component "LoanApprovalNotificationHandler" as LoanNotify
  component "TransactionConfirmationHandler" as TransferNotify
  component "OverdraftAlertHandler" as Overdraft
}

LoanSvc --> LoanSubmitted : creates
LoanSvc --> LoanDecision : creates
TransferSvc --> TransferDone : creates
AccountSvc --> AccountChanged : creates
InterestSvc --> InterestPosted : creates

LoanSubmitted --> EventDispatcher : dispatch
LoanDecision --> EventDispatcher : dispatch
TransferDone --> EventDispatcher : dispatch
AccountChanged --> EventDispatcher : dispatch
InterestPosted --> EventDispatcher : dispatch

EventDispatcher <|.. SyncBus
SyncBus --> Audit : all events
SyncBus --> LoanNotify : loan submitted
SyncBus --> TransferNotify : transfer completed
SyncBus --> Overdraft : overdraft detected

note right of SyncBus
Phase 1 uses synchronous in-process dispatch.
The interface allows a future async bus or queue.
end note

@enduml
